<div class="about-page">

  <!-- Page Hero -->
  <header class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="eyebrow">Credentials & Background</span>
      <h1>About Sidemount Authority</h1>
      <p>Creator of the AXIS Method. RAID Tech Trimix Sidemount Instructor. Crossover Instructor Trainer. RAID T.A.G. member. This is what the credentials mean — and what they cost to earn.</p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <!-- Credentials Grid -->
  <section class="credentials-section" aria-labelledby="credentials-heading">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="eyebrow">Qualifications</span>
      <h2 id="credentials-heading" style="margin-bottom:2rem; font-size:clamp(1.5rem,2.5vw,2rem);">Certifications &amp; Recognition</h2>

      <div class="credentials-grid">
      {% for cred in credentials.items %}
        <div class="credential-card">
          <span class="credential-agency">{{ cred.agency }}</span>
          <h3>{{ cred.credential }}</h3>
          <p>{{ cred.detail }}</p>
        </div>
        {% endfor %}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Bio Section -->
  <section class="bio-section" aria-labelledby="bio-heading">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="bio-grid">

        <div class="bio-image">
          <img
            src="/images/diver-eyecontact.webp"
            alt="Sidemount Authority instructor in open water"
            loading="lazy"
          />
        </div>

        <div class="bio-content">
          <span class="eyebrow">The Instructor</span>
          <h2 id="bio-heading">More Than a Configuration</h2>

          <p>Sidemount is a discipline that demands precision — in setup, in buoyancy, in mindset. I've spent years refining both my own skills and my ability to pass them on to others, from first-time sidemount divers through to experienced tech sidemount divers.</p>

          <p>As the creator of the AXIS Method, a RAID Tech Trimix Sidemount Instructor and RAID Crossover Instructor Trainer, I work with divers who are serious about doing it right. Not fashionably — correctly. There's a difference, and I care about that difference.</p>

          <p>The gear reviews and tips here are by-products of that commitment: honest assessments written after real dives on real kit, not after a briefing from a PR team. I will never recommend gear or brands that I do not fully believe in and/or use personally. </p>

          <a href="/contact/" class="btn btn-signal">Get in Touch</a>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Philosophy Section -->
  <section class="philosophy-section" aria-labelledby="philosophy-heading">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="eyebrow" style="text-align:center;display:block;">Philosophy</span>
      <h2 id="philosophy-heading" class="sr-only">Teaching Philosophy</h2>
      <blockquote class="philosophy-quote">
        Sidemount is not a shortcut, a trend, or a style choice. It is a configuration with logic behind it — and that logic only reveals itself when the system is aligned properly, and the diver understands why every piece of kit is exactly where it is.
      </blockquote>
    </div>
  </section>
